16 WHEREAS, police chiefs and heads of law enforcement agencies of Georgia support the
17 continuous elevation of standards and training of law enforcement managers and have been
18 instrumental in increasing the public's awareness of methods for avoiding being victims of
19 crime; and
20 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the police chiefs and heads of law
21 enforcement agencies of Georgia be recognized for their many personal sacrifices as well as
22 their outstanding and courageous contributions to the citizens of this state.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
24 the members of this body recognize March 6, 2025, as Police Chiefs and Heads of Law
25 Enforcement Agencies Day at the state capitol and commend each police chief and head of
26 a law enforcement agency in this state for his or her outstanding commitment to the people
27 of this state.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
29 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to Scott
30 Gray, President of the Georgia Association of Chiefs of Police, and A. A. Butch Ayers,
31 Executive Director of the Georgia Association of Chiefs of Police.
